message.en_US: Hi.
Hello. Did you need anything in particular?
[shakes head]
Very well. The back room and upper floor are currently closed for maintenance, but feel free to explore the lobby and any entries on display.
Bye!
Hello. Did you need something?
Excuse me?
Sorry.
...Oh! Your speech module is broken, isn't it?
[nods]
That's quite unfortunate. Though, I thought that issue was practically nonexistent now... \. Well, nevermind that.
Let's see... you asked me 'How', so how can we narrow that down better... Is it a question about the library?
[shakes head]
...About this area?
[shakes head]
Hm... about me?
[nods]
I'm sorry dear, but I'm not willing to answer any possible questions you could have about me.
...Though, I suppose if you really want to know about how I got here, maybe I can tell you a little bit about it if you help me out some.
You see, some troll somehow found their way into the back parts of the library and spawned dozens of enemies, so I can't access anything up there. Do you think you could help?
[nods]
Thank you, I really appreciate it. I'll go ahead and unlock the door for you.
...Oh, I almost forgot to ask, what's your name?
Lea!
Thank you in advance, Lea!
I see. Well, the offer still stands should you wish to know more about me.
And you return. I assume you've dealt with the problem upstairs?
[nods]
Good. It will be great to have access to that floor again.
In fact, I might be able to start working on \c[3]The Lost Zones Documentation Project\c[0] again...
I guess that would be up to you to decide. I would definitely need your help, at the very least.
Anyways. You wanted to know about me, right?
[nods]
I suppose I can spare you some small details about how I got here. You can't exactly tell anyone here, anyways.
...It was a few weeks ago. Quite a while before the modders guild first arrived.
I was glitch hunting in \c[3]Sapphire Ridge\c[0] when something... really strange happened.
It was like all of time had stopped, and all I heard was someone's voice... a woman, I think. She told me to "Find the Archivist in the north for answers."
I had no idea what had happened, or what she was talking about, at least, not until I found this place.
There's always been rumors of a 'secret hidden development archive' being somewhere in \c[3]The Playground\c[0], but most just shrugged it off as an unrealistic fantasy.
Ironically enough, it turns out it's fairly easy to find these \c[3]'Lost Zones'\c[0] given you know where to look for them, which is why I found this place long before anyone else.
When I arrived, there was seemingly no one to be found here. No Archivist, nothing. So, I decided to start looking through the Archives myself.
Interestingly enough, there seemed to be documentation about some sort of Archivist NPC that would run this place, but whatever happened to that NPC, they're not in the game anymore.
...And that's how I 'became the Archivist'. \. If you want to know more about me or the Archives, meet me on the second floor sometime and help me out again.
Bye!
Lea, I need you to keep an eye on the Archivist. She's almost definitely an \c[3]Evotar\c[0] judging by her description of what happened in Sapphire Ridge.
The fact that there are more Evotars out in \c[3]The Playground\c[0]... \. This could be bad.
We need to find out who's doing this, and why, before any \c[3]Evotars\c[0] suffer, or worse, they end up in the \c[3]Vermillion Wasteland\c[0].
[nods]

text.en_US: This place is crazy... you said modders have been adding to this area, right?
More or less. Apparently this area was scrapped during development.
You wanna know something weird about how the Modders' Guild found this place?
What, were the NPCs rogue or something?
Haha, no. \. Apparently no one knows who that Archivist lady is outside of the game, and she's definitely not an NPC or a maintenance worker.

message.en_US: Why?
Well, you might think that she could just be a lone wolf type, or someone who doesn't share her personal life, right?
Plenty of people are like that on CrossWorlds.
[nods]
And that's fair enough, especially considering that's originally what the modders thought too.
But apparently, not only was this 'Archivist' here before most mod and hacker forums had even discovered it...
She's been working on this library almost constantly, and no one sees her logout or sleep!
Alex, quit trying to peddle your weird conspiracy theories to people, you'll weird them out!
It's not a conspiracy theory, Tara! \. ...Sorry if I creeped you out, Miss...?
Lea!
Lea. \. Say, we're gonna check out Lavender Tower in a bit, would you be interested in accompanying me and Tara?
You don't have to answer now. If you're interested, just meet us by the door.
Lea, I think you should talk to this 'Archivist' person. \. Something tells me she's may be an \c[3]Evotar\c[0], but... \. What is she doing here, of all places?
a!
